im currently working on a new storing json system (which works atm i just need to reimplement the transactioncommands using it)... as a brief summary of what i've done:
I've turned the IRepository interface into a Cache abstract class which contains the majority of the implementation needed for both
I've made a new interface called Cacheable (if you can think of a better name then please tell me lmao i couldnt come up w a good name) which contains 3 methods: getId(), getName() and toFormattedString(). I've made this for the Cache abstract class so now basically the Cache now looks like this: public abstract class Cache<T extends Cacheable> which means when you iterate through the list you can access those methods from the Interface)
I've generified the LoadCategories and SaveCategories into LoadFromDBCommand<T extends Cacheable> and SaveToDBCommand<T extends Cacheable>...
Save was easy to generify just had to replace Category with T
Load was a bit harder... there's now a new class called CacheTypeFactory which gets the type based on the class of the Cacheable thing... it has a single method in it called getType(Class<? extends Cacheable> class) which gets the type based on what you specify
Also generic fixes 🙂
Fixed implementation of Transactions using new Database Storage system.

Abstracted Listing Transaction Command
Small fix on adding transactions.
